I would love to see a Browse Document Hierarchy as a tab to find the new location when moving a wiki document using Edit>>Location. This is in addition to the "Search, History, Recently Modified, Referring Pages" tabs.

Its operation should be identical to the document hierarchy browser in a page's Info tab except it would need both navigate-deeper/expand and select functionalities. The end result, of course, is a reference to the selected parent document being inserted in the location field.

AttachmentsSoapService doesn't close inputStream in getAttachmentData(long, String, int).

(AttachmentsSoapService:108) 
      FileUtils.copy(attachmentManager.getAttachmentData(attachment),baos);
      baos.close();

There is no use in closing baos, but input stream must be closed, as it could be a file stream, for example.

Should be something like this, I presume:
            InputStream inputStream = attachmentManager.getAttachmentData(attachment);
            FileUtils.copy(inputStream,baos);
            inputStream.close();

