Presently the {info} macro takes up a large percentage of the page as there is no mechanism of controlling the width or hight of the info box created.
Adding additional parameter would make it more customisable.

Start with the markup:

{code}
a
b
c
{code}

edit the page in rich text mode, and add a newline after 'a' and 'b'

Save the page, and the markup has become:

{code}
abc
{code}

This isn't 100% reproducible, but I have seen it in Firefox.
